ain by the Normans. In modern times it has been made famous by the English philosopher  Bertrand Russell  (  1872–1970 ), but is only in occasional use."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lord Bertrand de Comps was born about 1060, in Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, France, his father, Géraud de COMBS, was 26 and his mother, Marguerite de BERTRAND, was 17. He had at least 1 son with Béliarde de Salis."},"et":{"about 1060–":"umbes 1060–Surnud","1060–Male":"1060–Surnud","1070–Female":"1070–Surnud","1095–1163":"1095–1163","1035–Male":"1035–Surnud","1045–Female":"1045–Surnud","about 1060":"umbes 1060","about 1095":"umbes 1095","1035":"1035","1045":"1045","1163":"1163","1095":"1095","1060":"1060","1070":"1070","Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, FRANCE,":"Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, Prantsusmaa","Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, Provence, France":"Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1060–":"noin 1060–Kuollut","1060–Male":"1060–Kuollut","1070–Female":"1070–Kuollut","1095–1163":"1095–1163","1035–Male":"1035–Kuollut","1045–Female":"1045–Kuollut","about 1060":"noin 1060","about 1095":"noin 1095","1035":"1035","1045":"1045","1163":"1163","1095":"1095","1060":"1060","1070":"1070","Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur, FRANCE,":"Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, Ranska","Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, Provence, France":"Comps-sur-Artuby, Var, Ranska"},"fr":{"about 1060–":"environ 1060–Décédé","1060–Male":"1060–Décédé","1070–Female":"1070–Décédée","1095–1163":"1095–1163","1035–Male":"1035–Décédé","1045–Female":"1045–Décédée","about 1060":"environ 1060","about 1095":"environ 1095","103